headline: Why The Narrative Around Royal Caribbean Is Shifting After Recent Earnings And Analyst Revisions
summary: Royal Caribbean Cruises' latest earnings update has prompted analysts to nudge their fair value estimate slightly lower to about $331.04 per share, as they bake in marginally softer revenue growth and a higher required return in their models. While the long term growth story and balance sheet progress still look compelling to many, a slower trajectory for yields and reduced visibility into pricing are encouraging a more measured stance on the stock’s upside. Read on to see how you can follow...

headline: Heard on the Street Thursday Recap: Oracle's Outlook
summary: Tech fell behind. The Dow industrials surged a day after a Federal Reserve move viewed by some as a "dovish" rate cut. The Dow added 646 points, or 1.3%, to close at a record. The S&P 500 added just 0.

headline: 3 Volatile Stocks We’re Skeptical Of
